- Scope in programming means, the area (or context) in which a 
  declared variable is visible and accessible

- ( Examples of block scope ):
• if / else blocks
• for, while, and do...while loops
• Standalone { } blocks
• switch statements
• Function bodies (also technically block-scoped)

- ( Example of function scope ): the function itself ( self explanatory )

- ( var ): is a function scope variable 

- ( let & const ): are block scope variables